{"PubmedBookArticle": [], "PubmedArticle": [{"MedlineCitation": {"OtherAbstract": [], "CitationSubset": [], "OtherID": ["00009368"], "GeneralNote": [], "SpaceFlightMission": [], "KeywordList": [["NASA Discipline Plant Biology", "Non-NASA Center"]], "InvestigatorList": [[{"Identifier": [], "AffiliationInfo": [{"Identifier": [], "Affiliation": "Yale U, New Haven, CT"}], "LastName": "Galston", "ForeName": "A W", "Initials": "AW"}]], "PMID": "11539091", "DateCompleted": {"Year": "1998", "Month": "08", "Day": "28"}, "DateRevised": {"Year": "2019", "Month": "05", "Day": "14"}, "Article": {"Language": ["eng"], "ArticleDate": [], "ELocationID": [], "Journal": {"ISSN": "0032-0889", "JournalIssue": {"Volume": "82", "Issue": "3", "PubDate": {"Year": "1986"}}, "Title": "Plant physiology", "ISOAbbreviation": "Plant Physiol"}, "ArticleTitle": "Cadmium-induced accumulation of putrescine in oat and bean leaves.", "Pagination": {"StartPage": "641", "EndPage": "645", "MedlinePgn": "641-5"}, "Abstract": {"AbstractText": ["The effects of Cd2+ on putrescine (Put), spermidine (Spd), and spermine (Spm) titers were studied in oat and bean leaves. Treatment with Cd2+ for up to 16 hours in the light or dark resulted in a large increase in Put titer, but had little or no effect on Spd or Spm. The activity of arginine decarboxylase (ADC) followed the pattern of Put accumulation, and experiments with alpha-difluoromethylarginine established that ADC was the enzyme responsible for Put increase. Concentrations of Cd2+ as low as 10 micromolar increased Put titer in oat segments. In bean leaves, there was a Cd(2+)-induced accumulation of Put in the free and soluble conjugated fractions, but not in the insoluble fraction. This suggests a rapid exchange between Put that exists in the free form and Put found in acid soluble conjugate forms. It is concluded that Cd2+ can act like certain other stresses (K+ and Mg2+ deficiency, excess NH4+, low pH, salinity, osmotic stress, wilting) to induce substantial increases in Put in plant cells."]}, "AuthorList": [{"Identifier": [], "AffiliationInfo": [{"Identifier": [], "Affiliation": "Boyce Thompson Institute, Ithaca, New York 14853, USA."}], "LastName": "Weinstein", "ForeName": "L H", "Initials": "LH"}, {"Identifier": [], "AffiliationInfo": [], "LastName": "Kaur-Sawhney", "ForeName": "R", "Initials": "R"}, {"Identifier": [], "AffiliationInfo": [], "LastName": "Rajam", "ForeName": "M V", "Initials": "MV"}, {"Identifier": [], "AffiliationInfo": [], "LastName": "Wettlaufer", "ForeName": "S H", "Initials": "SH"}, {"Identifier": [], "AffiliationInfo": [], "LastName": "Galston", "ForeName": "A W", "Initials": "AW"}], "PublicationTypeList": ["Journal Article", "Research Support, Non-U.S. Gov't", "Research Support, U.S. Gov't, Non-P.H.S.", "Research Support, U.S. Gov't, P.H.S."]}, "MedlineJournalInfo": {"Country": "United States", "MedlineTA": "Plant Physiol", "NlmUniqueID": "0401224", "ISSNLinking": "0032-0889"}, "ChemicalList": [{"RegistryNumber": "0", "NameOfSubstance": "Polyamines"}, {"RegistryNumber": "2FZ7Y3VOQX", "NameOfSubstance": "Spermine"}, {"RegistryNumber": "69955-43-7", "NameOfSubstance": "alpha-(difluoromethyl)arginine"}, {"RegistryNumber": "94ZLA3W45F", "NameOfSubstance": "Arginine"}, {"RegistryNumber": "EC 4.1.1.-", "NameOfSubstance": "Carboxy-Lyases"}, {"RegistryNumber": "EC 4.1.1.17", "NameOfSubstance": "Ornithine Decarboxylase"}, {"RegistryNumber": "EC 4.1.1.19", "NameOfSubstance": "arginine decarboxylase"}, {"RegistryNumber": "J6K4F9V3BA", "NameOfSubstance": "Cadmium Chloride"}, {"RegistryNumber": "U87FK77H25", "NameOfSubstance": "Spermidine"}, {"RegistryNumber": "V10TVZ52E4", "NameOfSubstance": "Putrescine"}], "MeshHeadingList": [{"QualifierName": ["analogs & derivatives", "pharmacology"], "DescriptorName": "Arginine"}, {"QualifierName": ["drug effects", "enzymology", "metabolism"], "DescriptorName": "Avena"}, {"QualifierName": ["pharmacology"], "DescriptorName": "Cadmium Chloride"}, {"QualifierName": ["me